<html>
<body>
<p>If Mote.io is installed from Chrome app store, enter <b>chrome://extensions</b> in the address bar and click the checkmark next to Enabled to disable the official extension.</p>
<p>Download custom Mote.io Chrome extension from <a href="https://github.com/Kevin-Jin/mote.io-extension/archive/master.zip">here</a> and extract.</p>
<p>In <b>chrome://extensions</b>, check Developer mode at the top and select the <b>Load unpacked extension...</b> button.</p>
<p>Navigate to the mote.io-extension-master directory that was extracted from the .zip file and select it.</p>
<p>Install the Mote.io <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ianjennings.mote_io">Android</a> or <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/mote.io/id686305047">iOS</a> application on your mobile device.</p>
<p>Create a Mote.io account <a href="https://mote.io/">here</a> and sync it with your mobile device.</p>
<p>Visit <a href="http://www.pjtb.net/ezmoteio/configmaker.php">here</a> to make a new remote for a webpage on the www.pjtb.net domain and then visit <a href="http://www.pjtb.net/ezmoteio/chooseremoteable.php">here</a> to try out the remote. Because Mote.io is in beta and is unstable, the page may need to be refreshed a number of times before the remote works.</p>
</body>
</html>
